1.title: Index Portland
1.plot: Sumeet Kumar and Jordan Cardenas visit Index PDX, the most well-known sneaker consignment store in the Northwest, to talk to owner Terrance Ricketts and manager/custom shoe designer Cameron Kiyokawa about the come up of Index, selling a pair for $25,000, being on Complex's list of Top 10 sneaker reselling stores, and being in the sneaker capital, Portland.

2.title: Carl Tart: Part One
2.plot: Fresh off his flight from L.A., Carl Tart joins Sumeet Kumar and Jordan Cardenas at the studio to talk about his come up in Improv, being an actor on Lethal Weapon, being a writer on Brooklyn Nine-Nine, working alongside Terry Crews, and being a Black writer on network television. Only 4.8% of writers on network television are Black, and Carl is one of them.

3.title: Carl Tart: Part Two
3.plot: Fresh off his flight from L.A., Carl Tart joins Sumeet Kumar and Jordan Cardenas at the studio to talk about his come up in Improv, being an actor on Lethal Weapon, being a writer on Brooklyn Nine-Nine, working alongside Terry Crews, and being a Black writer on network television. Only 4.8% of writers on network television are Black, and Carl is one of them.

4.title: Deadstock Coffee
4.plot: The first ever sneaker-themed coffee shop has made noise in Portland, Oregon. We chop it up with owner and former Nike shoe developer, Ian Williams and former Nike employee, and current Hypebarista, Kevin Minnieweather, at Deadstock Coffee. We talk about designing and developing a Nike SB Dunk, creating a space for the community to come and hang out, making amazing coffee, and being a key part of the sneaker culture in Portland.

5.title: Marcus Harvey: Owner of Portland Gear
5.plot: We chop it up with Marcus Harvey, owner of Portland Gear, one of Portland's apparel brands with a mix of hype, creativity, and relationship to the city. We talk to him about his love for Nike, being creative, struggling with anxiety, the obsession with social media, creating one of Portland's most well-known apparel brands, and so much more.

imdb.title: In the Culture
plot: Entertainers Sumeet Kumar and Jordan Cardenas talk to dope people doing dope things. We explore what they're doing for the culture and chop it up about their lives.
